18    /**
19    * <p>
20    * A {@link java.lang.ClassLoader} that is capable of loading explicitly defined classes. The class loader will free
21    * any binary resources once a class that is defined by its binary data is loaded. This class loader is thread safe since
22    * the class loading mechanics are only called from synchronized context.
23    * </p>
24    * <p>
25    * <b>Note</b>: Instances of this class loader return URLs for their represented class loaders with the <i>bytebuddy</i> schema.
26    * These URLs do not represent URIs as two classes with the same name yield identical URLs but might represents different byte
27    * arrays.
28    * </p>
29    */

96    /**
97    * Creates a new class loader for a given definition of classes.
98    *
99    * @param parent The {@link java.lang.ClassLoader} that is the parent of this class loader.
100    * @param typeDefinitions A map of type descriptions pointing to their binary representations.
101    * @param protectionDomain The protection domain to apply where {@code null} references an implicit protection domain.
102    * @param accessControlContext The access control context to use for loading classes.
103    * @param persistenceHandler The persistence handler to be used by the created class loader.
104    * @param packageDefinitionStrategy The package definer to be queried for package definitions.
